@dbinetti - I can't reproduce this, I'm afraid. I ran the collectstatic command twice. The first time, everything was uploaded. The second time, nothing was uploaded as all the files were unmodified.

It occurs to me that this may be to do with Heroku's temporary filesystem. Django skips uploading a file if the local path's modification time is less than the remote file's modification time. If Heroku is checking out your project each time, then the timestamps will be newer than the files on S3.

Try running collectstatic from your local filesystem twice.

